{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place garlic, oregano, coriander (leaves, stems and roots), chilli, onion, cumin and olive oil into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <nobr>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Squeeze the juice from lime halves into a bowl, then add lime juice to mixing bowl with the squeezed lime halves.","Add chicken, water and stock paste and cook <nobr>10 min\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>. Remove squeezed lime halves with a slotted spoon, then squeeze well before discarding.","Add corn and kidney beans and cook <nobr>4 min\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>.","Divide soup between 6 large serving bowls, then top with tomato, spring onion\/shallot, capsicum, avocado and cabbage. Serve soup immediately with corn chips, sour cream, jalapeños and extra coriander leaves."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["4 garlic cloves","3 sprigs fresh oregano, leaves only","4 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves, stems and roots, plus extra leaves for garnishing (see Tips)","1 long red chilli, deseeded if preferred","1 brown onion, (approx. 150 g), cut into halves","1 tsp ground cumin","1 tbsp olive oil","2 limes, cut into halves","350 g skinless chicken thigh fillets, cut into cubes (2 cm)","750 g water","2 tbsp Chicken stock paste  (see Tips)","400 g canned corn kernels, rinsed and drained (weight is pre-draining)","400 g canned kidney beans, rinsed and drained (weight is pre-draining)","190 g fresh tomatoes, finely diced","2 spring onions\/shallots, trimmed and sliced","140 g red capsicum, deseeded and diced","240 g avocado, flesh only, sliced","180 g cabbage, shredded","corn chips, to serve","sour cream, to serve","marinated jalapeño chillies (jarred), to serve"]}],"id":"r78369","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-hXWQ6gTberQ\/XZMyPhj-loI\/AAAAAAAAaiY\/vkH9MuzGnGcyRu4ISWKNGIcHM8UwJMwGgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_7aYhNC1OvYMxLbks.png","title":"Mexican chicken soup","publishedAt":"2